message.content: One of the most significant events that took place in Brunei in the past 5 years was the implementation of Sharia law in April 2019. This marked a major development in the legal system of the country, introducing strict Islamic laws and punishments for various offenses, including adultery, theft, and same-sex relationships. The move drew widespread international attention and sparked debates on human rights, particularly regarding the treatment of the LGBTQ+ community.
